<statement><div><p>A rectangular chalk box with no lid has dimensions of <m>{12} \,\text{cm}</m> in length, <m>{47} \, \text{cm}</m> in width, and <m>{44} \, \text{cm}</m> in height. What is its total external surface area?</p>








<p><m>\text{Surface area }=</m><fillin characters="9" name="ans1"/><m>\text{cm}^2</m></p>

<p hidden=""> </p></div></statement>
<solution><div><p>For a rectangular open box (open at the top), the surface area consists of:</p>
<p/><ol><li>Base (bottom): <m>L \times W</m></li>
<li>Two sides: <m>2(L \times H)</m></li>
<li>Front and back: <m>2(W \times H)</m></li></ol>
<p>Therefore the formula is:</p>
<p><m>\text{Surface Area} = (L \times W)+2(L \times H)+2(W \times H)</m></p>
<p>Given:</p>
<p/><ol><li><m>\text{length}={12}\, \text{cm}</m></li>
<li><m>\text{width}={47}\, \text{cm}</m></li>
<li><m>\text{height}={44}\, \text{cm}</m></li></ol>
<p>Substitute values in the formula.</p>
<p><md>
<mrow>\text{Surface Area}\amp  = ({12} \times {47})+2({12} \times {44})+2({47} \times {44})</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {564}+2({528})+2({2068})</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {564}+{1056}+ {4136}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {\color{blue}{5756} }\, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
</md></p>
<p>Therefore,</p>
<p><m>\text{The external surface area of the open chalk box is} \, {\color{blue}{5756} }\, \text{cm}^2</m></p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>5756</m></p></answer>
